SPEAKER of the National Assembly Jacob Mudenda has suspended independent Norton legislator Temba Mliswa for disorderly conduct, the Daily News reports. Jacob Mudenda imposed a ban for six sittings from Parliament against Mliswa for interjecting other MPs when making contributions and ministers responding to questions from legislators. This is the first time  the august House has  put into use the newly approved measures in the Standing Orders which were adopted by Parliament a fortnight ago allowing a presiding officer to preclude a legislator from attending sittings for a prescribed period.  More to follow…